cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a framework for subspace clustering, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves optimizing a reward function, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of a data structure called the triplet relationship, which is a novel contribution and could be of interest to researchers in the field of similarity search (cs.SI).
